01:01:10,983 --> 01:01:16,067
With a vote of six in the affirmative and one absent, the motion passes.

894
01:01:16,604 --> 01:01:19,325
15-750 offered by Councilor Knight.

895
01:01:20,145 --> 01:01:28,548
Be it resolved that the City Council request the implementation of pedestrian crossing controls at the intersection of George and Main Street.

896
01:01:28,608 --> 01:01:29,248
Councilor Knight.

897
01:01:30,168 --> 01:01:32,729
Mr. President, I think that this resolution speaks for itself.

898
01:01:33,069 --> 01:01:39,771
I got a call from a couple of constituents, one of whom is in the room this evening, whose birthday may be coming up, if I understand correctly.

899
01:01:40,431 --> 01:01:42,712
And this is an issue of importance to them.

900
01:01:42,732 --> 01:01:45,573
And I think it's an issue, it should be an issue of importance to us as well, Mr. President.

901
01:01:46,135 --> 01:01:51,417
The 101 bus, for example, travels up and down Main Street all day long, and it makes stops right at George Street in Maine.

902
01:01:52,098 --> 01:02:02,663
There are no pedestrian crossing controls at George Street in Maine, which is a heavily traveled thoroughfare, and buses along that route have pretty high ridership, Mr. President.

903
01:02:03,003 --> 01:02:07,025
So in the interest of public safety and keeping our pedestrians safe, I brought this resolution forward.

904
01:02:07,065 --> 01:02:08,365
I think it's a good idea.

905
01:02:10,225 --> 01:02:13,287
long in the waiting, but it's something that's necessary.

906
01:02:13,327 --> 01:02:22,094
And as the sun goes down a little bit earlier here, and people are getting home from work at 4, 5, and 6 o'clock at night when it's dark out, it highlights the problem even more, Mr. President.

907
01:02:22,114 --> 01:02:25,577
So I'd ask that my fellow colleagues support me in voting in the affirmative for the resolution.

908
01:02:25,597 --> 01:02:32,082
I'd like to add that now, the result of an effort by our own councillor, Penta.

909
01:02:33,302 --> 01:02:34,724
Ma'am, you wish to address the council.

910
01:02:34,764 --> 01:02:36,245
Please state your name and address for the record.

911
01:02:36,645 --> 01:02:37,185
I would, sir.

912
01:02:37,205 --> 01:02:37,926
Thank you very much.

913
01:02:47,175 --> 01:02:47,976
Okay, thanks.

914
01:02:48,717 --> 01:02:53,182
Hi, I'm Rachel Tandenhouse, 26 Pearl Street, Medford.

915
01:02:54,363 --> 01:02:56,586
I would like to speak in support of this.

916
01:02:57,347 --> 01:03:01,412
I live around the corner from there, from Georgia, Maine.

917
01:03:01,992 --> 01:03:03,572
It is a major bus stop for me.

918
01:03:03,592 --> 01:03:04,853
The 96 goes there.

919
01:03:04,873 --> 01:03:06,013
The 101 goes there.

920
01:03:06,053 --> 01:03:08,234
Those are the buses that pass closest to my house.

921
01:03:08,674 --> 01:03:14,515
And that's how I get to work every day, is by the 101 or the 96.

922
01:03:14,955 --> 01:03:16,276
I'm also blind.

923
01:03:18,836 --> 01:03:20,997
And I think I get around pretty okay.

924
01:03:21,077 --> 01:03:22,397
And I do my best.

925
01:03:22,477 --> 01:03:25,578
And I have this awesome guide dog here that helps me out.

926
01:03:27,158 --> 01:03:30,459
But some intersections are certainly more challenging than others.

927
01:03:31,608 --> 01:03:33,331
And this is absolutely one of them.

928
01:03:34,412 --> 01:03:37,056
It's a really difficult one to navigate.

929
01:03:37,697 --> 01:03:41,583
Nobody, whether you can see or not, can really tell what's coming around a corner.

930
01:03:42,595 --> 01:03:45,297
And people come zooming through.

931
01:03:45,558 --> 01:03:49,721
And just some sort of, I mean, I would be very excited about a traffic light.

932
01:03:50,181 --> 01:03:53,104
But some sort of traffic calming measure would be pretty exciting.

933
01:03:54,945 --> 01:03:57,767
I think that that would do a lot for my safety and my independence.

934
01:03:58,988 --> 01:04:04,993
And frankly, the cars don't really care if they run over a blind person or a sighted one, so I bet it would do wonders for everybody else too.

935
01:04:06,134 --> 01:04:10,298
And I appreciate very much your bringing this up.

936
01:04:11,408 --> 01:04:12,929
love Medford very, very much.

937
01:04:13,229 --> 01:04:14,890
Um, it occasionally tries to kill me.

938
01:04:15,671 --> 01:04:17,752
And, um, well, I know it's not personal.

939
01:04:18,473 --> 01:04:25,538
Uh, you know, this is one of the intersections that would, uh, do wonders for my safety and, and that of my neighbors.

940
01:04:25,598 --> 01:04:29,340
And if you ever want to hear about any of the other ones, you know, let me know.

941
01:04:30,801 --> 01:04:31,002
Thanks.

942
01:04:31,042 --> 01:04:31,502
Thank you.

943
01:04:31,602 --> 01:04:34,444
On the motion approved by council and I'd all those in favor.

944
01:04:35,164 --> 01:04:36,065
Oh, madam vice president.

945
01:04:36,105 --> 01:04:36,746
You want to speak on this?

946
01:04:36,806 --> 01:04:37,326
I apologize.

947
01:04:37,504 --> 01:04:38,945
Quickly, thank you, President De La Russo.

948
01:04:38,985 --> 01:04:40,965
I think it's a very good resolution.

949
01:04:41,065 --> 01:04:43,226
I also got a couple emails this week on it.

950
01:04:43,566 --> 01:04:57,772
It reminds me of Winthrop and George a couple years ago where we had a couple, I believe somebody was injured very badly at that intersection and we did traffic calming approaches.

951
01:04:57,832 --> 01:05:01,273
We installed a raised crosswalk very close by.

952
01:05:01,373 --> 01:05:06,915
So this is parallel to that and definitely a speedway that needs some attention.

953
01:05:08,740 --> 01:05:10,021
You wish to speak on this matter?

954
01:05:11,622 --> 01:05:12,163
Councilor Knight?

955
01:05:12,703 --> 01:05:18,428
If we could also send this paper to the Pedestrian Committee to add to one of their list of intersections of concern, I'd appreciate it.

956
01:05:19,288 --> 01:05:22,931
So that this be sent to the Pedestrian Committee?

957
01:05:23,151 --> 01:05:24,412
Yes.

958
01:05:24,713 --> 01:05:24,873
Ms.

959
01:05:24,913 --> 01:05:32,599
McGivern has been working with the Pedestrian Committee to implement some safety controls in our community to make Medford a safer place for those who choose to walk.

960
01:05:32,919 --> 01:05:33,260
Very good.

961
01:05:33,320 --> 01:05:37,583
So on the motion of Councilor Knight, as amended by Councilor Knight, that this paper be sent

962
01:05:37,987 --> 01:05:39,227
to the pedestrian committee.

963
01:05:39,588 --> 01:05:41,888
Did the vice president have a amendment there too?

964
01:05:42,789 --> 01:05:42,969
No.

965
01:05:43,509 --> 01:05:45,590
Sir, please state your name and address for the record.

966
01:05:46,810 --> 01:05:48,971
My name is Mario Martin from 198 Harvard.

967
01:05:49,811 --> 01:05:52,572
And I actually think this is a really good resolution.

968
01:05:53,032 --> 01:05:58,714
But I was wondering, because basically on Main Street, there are several stops.

969
01:05:59,775 --> 01:06:05,817
And I was actually wondering if, in addition to this, would there be some sort of possibility where we can, you know,

970
01:06:06,788 --> 01:06:13,471
offer sidewalks on pretty much all of the bus stops on Main Street and South Medford as well.

971
01:06:13,811 --> 01:06:27,837
More particularly, I think it's Wellesley Street, the corner of Wellesley Street and Main Street, where I know that there's an elderly couple that lives on Main Street that usually tries to cross the street.

972
01:06:27,857 --> 01:06:33,419
And as I forget who mentioned it, but at nighttime, it's incredibly difficult to cross the street.

973
01:06:33,439 --> 01:06:35,480
Well, I mean, it's incredibly dangerous.

974
01:06:36,536 --> 01:06:37,757
So there's people flying through.

975
01:06:38,097 --> 01:06:50,642
So I would also if possible, um, you know, seek to ask, see if it's, see if it's, uh, if, if, if, if you guys can, you know, add, uh, all of us stops on mainstream as well.

976
01:06:52,483 --> 01:06:53,483
Uh, thank you.

977
01:06:53,503 --> 01:06:53,823
Thank you.

978
01:06:54,284 --> 01:06:54,604
Thank you.

979
01:06:55,824 --> 01:07:04,508
On the motion of council night as amended by council night, all those in favor, all those opposed motion passes.

980
01:07:05,095 --> 01:07:07,536
15-751 offered by Councillor Penta.

981
01:07:07,976 --> 01:07:12,618
Be it resolved that the lack of timely action regarding Medford Square bus stops be discussed.

982
01:07:12,998 --> 01:07:13,678
Councillor Penta.

983
01:07:13,818 --> 01:07:18,440
Mr. President, this is not a new subject matter, at least for me.

984
01:07:18,580 --> 01:07:21,801
And it's getting more and more disturbing the more we keep thinking about it.

985
01:07:21,821 --> 01:07:25,002
I first introduced this subject matter back on June 14, 2011.

986
01:07:26,782 --> 01:07:34,045
First time I introduced this idea of the bus stops in the square with an anticipation that there was going to be a lot of road work and bridge work and construction.

987
01:07:34,627 --> 01:07:42,311
And bringing forward, I have a whole folder here of not only resolutions, but I have a folder of information coming back and going forth, whatever it might be.

988
01:07:43,452 --> 01:07:45,373
No resolution to the matter still as of yet.

989
01:07:45,533 --> 01:07:57,199
And then on June 30th of this year, resolution 15525, once again offered by myself, as it related not only to the bus stops, but a meeting with the DOT people, the MBTA,

990
01:07:58,573 --> 01:08:07,695
letting the governor of the Commonwealth know of our disappointment and our frustration over the idea of this bridge and its impact it's going to have here and the city of Medford, still no response.

991
01:08:07,735 --> 01:08:10,736
I asked the city clerk for a copy of the letter, never got a copy of the letter.

992
01:08:11,496 --> 01:08:18,798
Then again, on June 23rd of this, June, September, excuse me, on September 22nd of this year, I offered another resolution.

993
01:08:18,918 --> 01:08:20,579
Did they meet with us?

994
01:08:21,119 --> 01:08:21,299
No.

995
01:08:22,219 --> 01:08:23,339
They met with us this spring.

996
01:08:24,880 --> 01:08:25,520
This was June.

997
01:08:26,295 --> 01:08:27,695
We're talking about now September.

998
01:08:27,715 --> 01:08:30,276
We have had no meetings since June 30th to September.

999
01:08:31,776 --> 01:08:46,639
As a result of that, as a result of that in the Craddock Bridge, and I had asked you, Mr. President, on September 22nd to go forward and for the purposes of setting up a meeting with the MassDOT, letting them know and letting us know that we would have a committee of the whole.

1000
01:08:47,279 --> 01:08:50,540
I asked for a copy of the letter and apparently no letter was ever sent out.

1001
01:08:51,462 --> 01:08:59,866
So now, with no letters going out, and we're just sitting here spinning our wheels and just talking about something that's having a major effect.

1002
01:09:00,266 --> 01:09:05,428
Last weekend, the downtown Meffitt Square, we were around 8, 7.30, 8, 9 o'clock at night.

1003
01:09:05,988 --> 01:09:10,790
Unbeknownst to any business merchant down there, all of a sudden, everything was closed down because they were putting the bridge in.

1004
01:09:10,810 --> 01:09:13,251
They were putting the bridge in early in the night.

1005
01:09:13,271 --> 01:09:16,793
And one particular business not only had it closed down and lost all his, probably,

1006
01:09:17,383 --> 01:09:18,864
$3,000 to $4,000 worth of business.

1007
01:09:20,625 --> 01:09:21,766
It just doesn't make any sense.

1008
01:09:22,046 --> 01:09:27,090
Again, it's a lack of transparency, a lack of communication.

1009
01:09:28,250 --> 01:09:30,932
What's the sense of us having these resolutions?

1010
01:09:31,332 --> 01:09:34,355
You turned around and told us last week, we're going to get it resolved.

1011
01:09:34,695 --> 01:09:36,276
We haven't gotten nothing resolved, Fred.

1012
01:09:36,796 --> 01:09:37,577
Nothing's resolved.

1013
01:09:37,877 --> 01:09:39,198
We got no letters going out.

1014
01:09:39,558 --> 01:09:40,639
We have no meetings set up.

1015
01:09:41,480 --> 01:09:43,681
And we have bus concerns issues in the square.

1016
01:09:44,221 --> 01:09:47,721
And I believe it was last week, on one particular day, they even changed the buses.

1017
01:09:48,042 --> 01:09:51,762
And people had to walk to Meffitt Square not knowing that the buses had been changed.

1018
01:09:52,683 --> 01:10:02,545
All we're asking for is a little bit of common sense in this whole process of this Mystic, of this Kratik Bridge, you know, reconstruction, whatever it might be.

1019
01:10:03,181 --> 01:10:08,663
And another reason, if anybody's out there watching this whole thing, the reason it's taking two and a half years is because they don't work there every day.

1020
01:10:09,363 --> 01:10:12,144
They were supposed to be working there six days a week, double shifts.

1021
01:10:12,224 --> 01:10:12,864
That was the deal.

1022
01:10:13,164 --> 01:10:15,705
I don't even know what that contract says if they're not doing that.

1023
01:10:16,225 --> 01:10:19,767
But once again, it's another typical City of Medford contract for 121 feet.

1024
01:10:19,967 --> 01:10:22,848
121 feet is going to take two and a half years.

1025
01:10:23,168 --> 01:10:29,670
With the state of technology that's out there today, moving wires, telephone lines and gas lines, it just doesn't make any sense.

1026
01:10:30,340 --> 01:10:36,745
But I'm more concerned over the fact, the abruptness that's going to take place once those buses have to be moved.

1027
01:10:36,925 --> 01:10:41,889
And nobody has come to the city from the MassDOT, from the MBTA.

1028
01:10:42,389 --> 01:10:43,410
No letters have gone out.

1029
01:10:43,550 --> 01:10:48,714
Council resolutions have been ignored and not adhered to for the disposition of what takes place.

1030
01:10:48,834 --> 01:10:58,121
I don't know what's going on, but I certainly hope that the next city council coming in has a better firm and a better grip on their own resolutions, because this is absolutely making no sense at all.

1031
01:10:58,407 --> 01:11:00,408
We're making resolutions and there's no action taken.

1032
01:11:01,428 --> 01:11:03,169
So why are we making these resolutions?

1033
01:11:03,189 --> 01:11:03,629
Will you tell me?

1034
01:11:05,290 --> 01:11:07,031
You can't answer it, because I can't answer it.

1035
01:11:07,671 --> 01:11:10,312
And the fact of the matter is, this is what people elect us to do.

1036
01:11:10,872 --> 01:11:15,655
If we're going to do the people's business and we're going to talk about it, at least do what our own business tells us to do.

1037
01:11:16,035 --> 01:11:17,775
At least adhere to our own resolutions.

1038
01:11:18,476 --> 01:11:23,438
If a letter went out to the MBTA and they ignored it, they didn't want to come back, or DOT, so be it.

1039
01:11:24,965 --> 01:11:26,425
You're the chairperson of the council.

1040
01:11:26,665 --> 01:11:27,706
The letter should have gone out.

1041
01:11:27,846 --> 01:11:30,046
And the letter should have been addressed to the city clerk.

1042
01:11:30,086 --> 01:11:30,766
It should have gone out.

1043
01:11:31,307 --> 01:11:36,608
And if people are just getting lax around here and just letting resolutions come and go, well, then shame on everyone.

1044
01:11:38,048 --> 01:11:39,388
That's not what we're elected to do.

1045
01:11:40,089 --> 01:11:45,530
If you owned a business in Medford Square, and you had to figure out when you woke up in the morning, you had to turn that key.

1046
01:11:45,830 --> 01:11:49,051
And from the moment you turn that key, you've got to pay for the electric.

1047
01:11:49,071 --> 01:11:50,091
You've got to pay for the gas.

1048
01:11:50,362 --> 01:11:51,582
You've got to pay for the insurance.

1049
01:11:51,842 --> 01:11:53,523
You've got to pay for your stock.

1050
01:11:53,543 --> 01:11:57,564
You've got to pay for your employees, workman's comp, every other thing that goes along with it.

1051
01:11:58,264 --> 01:12:06,407
And then you come down and you have your business closed down or being given no information of when it's going to be closed down, no transparency, no communication.

1052
01:12:06,447 --> 01:12:11,148
Not one person from this city building went down to Medford Square to tell those business merchants.

1053
01:12:11,728 --> 01:12:17,970
And if the state was ignorant enough not to tell the business merchants or to tell the city hall, then the city should have been all over them.

1054
01:12:18,582 --> 01:12:19,822
all over them and they weren't.

1055
01:12:20,402 --> 01:12:28,524
But this city council is just as much to blame because they didn't call the meeting that was supposed to be called from June of this year till again on September 22nd.

1056
01:12:28,604 --> 01:12:29,565
And this is now November 17.

1057
01:12:31,065 --> 01:12:36,666
I'm going to ask you, Mr. President, since it's obvious that the city clerk, would you please call this meeting ASAP?

1058
01:12:36,907 --> 01:12:39,267
You said you were the last time we had this conversation.

1059
01:12:39,607 --> 01:12:42,908
It needs to be done before a business person goes out of business.

1060
01:12:45,204 --> 01:12:46,604
On the motion of Councilor Penta.

1061
01:12:46,644 --> 01:12:48,025
Roll call vote, Mr. President.

1062
01:12:50,646 --> 01:12:51,766
Transportation meeting is going to take place.

1063
01:12:52,526 --> 01:12:58,748
And amended by Councilor Knight that we get an update when the subcommittee on transportation is going to meet.

1064
01:13:00,069 --> 01:13:05,550
On that motion that roll call, Madam Clerk, please call the roll on the motion of Councilor Penta.

1065
01:13:05,570 --> 01:13:10,592
The roll call vote, Mr. President, is going to be that the city, you, Mr. President, you call the meeting.

1066
01:13:11,052 --> 01:13:11,712
You call the meeting.

1067
01:13:11,732 --> 01:13:12,973
You get in touch with DOT.

1068
01:13:13,013 --> 01:13:14,093
You get in call the MBTA.

1069
01:13:14,439 --> 01:13:19,161
and just tell them they've either been lax or they can use the excuse that they never got it.

1070
01:13:19,482 --> 01:13:30,647
We need to have a meeting ASAP because there is a concern relative to the businesses in Medford Square and to the people of this community not knowing when and how these bus stops are going to be moved and where they're going to be moved.

1071
01:13:31,247 --> 01:13:35,850
As amended by Councilor Knight to request when the next meeting.

1072
01:13:35,890 --> 01:13:38,031
Separate, sever the motion, Mr. President.

1073
01:13:39,411 --> 01:13:40,892
Request to sever the motion.

1074
01:13:41,712 --> 01:13:42,633
Mr. President, I have a question.

1075
01:13:43,385 --> 01:13:47,469
Um, have you had any correspondence at all with anybody from dot to date relative to the issue?

1076
01:13:48,149 --> 01:13:48,449
I have.

1077
01:13:49,610 --> 01:13:53,634
And, uh, would you be so kind as to report back to the council as to how those conversations have gone?

1078
01:13:54,014 --> 01:14:08,607
I'd be delighted if given the chance council night, there'll be a meeting on Tuesday, uh, December 1st with representatives of the department of transportation, uh, in at Alia pertaining to the credit bridge project.

1079
01:14:09,027 --> 01:14:09,167
No.

1080
01:14:09,207 --> 01:14:11,229
What about the MBTA, which is the bus stops?

1081
01:14:11,858 --> 01:14:18,582
The bus stop people have not expressed a willingness to attend a meeting of the city council.

1082
01:14:18,622 --> 01:14:19,442
Do you have that in writing?

1083
01:14:19,462 --> 01:14:22,143
Do you have a letter that you sent to them or is it just phone calls?

1084
01:14:22,444 --> 01:14:22,824
Phone calls.

1085
01:14:23,004 --> 01:14:23,364
Phone calls.

1086
01:14:23,384 --> 01:14:29,867
Well, could you please put it in writing so we could have a paper trail that allows us now to do what we need to do for leverage.

1087
01:14:30,308 --> 01:14:33,029
Common sense would tell you this is a business proposition.

1088
01:14:33,049 --> 01:14:36,051
This isn't a social phone call to say, would you please come?

1089
01:14:36,671 --> 01:14:38,472
Listen, they work for us, the taxpayers.

1090
01:14:38,878 --> 01:14:39,658
We don't work for them.

1091
01:14:39,718 --> 01:14:40,519
They work for us.

1092
01:14:41,259 --> 01:14:42,839
And the bus stops are very important.

1093
01:14:43,320 --> 01:14:49,622
They're important to not only to the commuters who use them every day, but they're also important to the business people that are in that square.

1094
01:14:49,642 --> 01:14:50,402
And if they have to be moved.

1095
01:14:50,802 --> 01:15:01,606
Maybe the construction people will explain in their presentation the scheduling for moving of the bus stop as it's part of the construction plan.

1096
01:15:01,626 --> 01:15:01,926
I don't know.

1097
01:15:02,106 --> 01:15:04,587
The Memphis City Council is the only people that can move bus stops.

1098
01:15:05,147 --> 01:15:06,548
DOT doesn't tell you they're going to move them.

1099
01:15:06,568 --> 01:15:07,668
MBTA doesn't tell you they're going to move them.

1100
01:15:08,186 --> 01:15:11,288
You need to have a discussion with them so they are aware of what we're going to do.

1101
01:15:11,568 --> 01:15:16,591
This council has to agree amongst themselves where those bus stops are going to go, and they're going to have to adhere to it.

1102
01:15:17,892 --> 01:15:19,633
We've been through this over and over again.

1103
01:15:19,653 --> 01:15:25,957
Any move, Mr. President, that you include the MBTA at this meeting?

1104
01:15:27,218 --> 01:15:29,800
